== Television series ==

=== Season 1 (2009â2010) ===
{{main|Stargate Universe (season 1)}}
{{Anchor|Season 1}}The first season consists of 20 episodes.<ref name=jm_090124>{{cite web|last=Mallozzi|first=Joseph|authorlink=Joseph Mallozzi|url=http://josephmallozzi.wordpress.com/2009/01/24/january-24-2009-to-haggis-or-not-to-haggis/|title=January 24, 2009: To Haggis or Not to Haggis?|work=josephmallozzi.wordpress.com|date=January 24, 2009|accessdate=January 25, 2009}}</ref> Brad Wright and Robert C. Cooper wrote the three-parter series opener named "Air", which was originally planned to be a two-parter.<ref name=jm_081111>{{cite web|last=Mallozzi|first=Joseph|authorlink=Joseph Mallozzi|url=http://josephmallozzi.wordpress.com/2008/11/11/november-11-2008-spinning-stargte-universe-day-one/|title=November 11, 2008: Spinning Stargate: Universe&nbsp;â Day One|work=josephmallozzi.wordpress.com|date=November 11, 2008|accessdate=November 13, 2008}}</ref> The first two parts of "Air" premiered on Syfy on October 2, 2009, with regularly weekly airing beginning on October 9, 2009.<ref name=syfyairdates>{{cite web|url=http://scifiwire.com/2009/07/syfy-sets-fall-premiere-d.php|title=Syfy sets fall premiere dates, schedule|date=July 20, 2009|accessdate=July 20, 2009|publisher=Sci Fi Wire}}</ref> "Fire" was originally going to be the title for episode four, but the story and script was too big to be able to fit into one episode, so the producers changed it to become a two-parter called "Darkness" and "Light", therefore pushing all future episodes forward one slot. "Justice" was the mid-season finale. The back half of the first season aired on Friday April 2, 2010 on Space and Syfy.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gateworld.net/news/2009/05/sgu-sets-fire-to-a-2-parter/|title=SGU sets 'Fire' to a 2-parter|first=Darren|last=Sumner|date=May 29, 2009|accessdate=May 29, 2009|publisher=[[GateWorld]]}}</ref>

British channel [[Sky1]] acquired the exclusive UK rights to ''Stargate Universe'' and began airing the series from October 6, 2009.<ref>{{cite press release|url= http://www.skypressoffice.co.uk/SkyOne/news/showarticle.asp?id=2784&month=8&year=2009|title= Sky1 HD Welcomes the Highly Anticipated Next Chapter in the Stargate Franchise, SGU: Stargate Universe, Starring Robert Carlyle|date=August 21, 2009|accessdate=August 24, 2009|publisher=Sky Press Office}}</ref> The series currently airs on [[Space (TV channel)|Space]] in Canada.<ref name="gw090420">{{cite web|last=Sumner|first=Darren|url=http://www.gateworld.net/news/2009/04/cooper-sgu-has-gay-characters/|title=Cooper: SGU has gay characters|publisher=[[GateWorld]]|date=April 20, 2009|accessdate=April 20, 2009}}</ref> In Australia ''Stargate Universe'' commenced airing on free-to-air-TV on [[Network Ten]] from 20:30 on Monday 14 December 2009, broadcasting the first two episodes: "Air (Part 1)" and "Air (Part 2)" as a movie-length premiere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stargate-universe.com.au/|title=Official Stargate Website: Home for all things Stargate - Universe, Atlantis, SG-1|work=Stargate-universe.com.au|accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref> However, Network Ten dropped the series after just three weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2009/12/gone-stargate-universe-supernatural.html|title=Gone: Stargate Universe, Supernatural|publisher=TV Tonight|accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref> All available episodes were however fast-tracked from the US and broadcast on the [[Sci Fi Channel (Australia)|Sci Fi Channel]] on [[Foxtel]] screening in Australia only 'days' after the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifitv.com.au/Shows/StargateUniverse|title=Official Stargate Website: Home for all things Stargate - Universe, Atlantis, SG-1|work=Scifitv.com.au|accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref>
{{:Stargate Universe (season 1)}}<!--Dear editor: Please go to [[Stargate Universe (season 1)]] to edit the episode summaries.-->

The final episode of Season 1, "Incursion (Part 2)", had World Premiere on the German TV channel "RTL2". RTL2 aired the episode one week ahead of SyFy.

=== Season 2 (2010â2011) ===
{{main|Stargate Universe (season 2)}}
{{Anchor|Season 2}}The second season of ''[[Stargate Universe]]'' was announced by [[Syfy]] on December 13, 2009. Like the first season, the second season consisted of 20 episodes. Nine episodes had already been reserved by the primary series writers. The series was moved from the franchise's usual time on Friday to Tuesday, along with ''[[Caprica (TV series)|Caprica]]''. This is due to Syfy picking up [[WWE Friday Night SmackDown]].<ref name="Series_Move">{{cite web|url=http://www.gateworld.net/news/2010/04/sgu-other-syfy-dramas-moving-to-tuesdays/|title=SGU, other Syfy dramas moving to Tuesdays
 |first=Darren|last=Sumner|date=April 15, 2010|publisher=Gateworld|accessdate=June 12, 2010}}</ref> The series resumed on September 28, 2010, USA.<ref name=airdates>{{cite web|url=http://www.syfy.com/schedule/index.php?search_text=Stargate%20Universe|title=Syfy Schedule; Stargate Universe|accessdate=September 11, 2010|publisher=Syfy}}</ref>  In Ireland & UK the series resumed on October 5 at 9pm on Sky1 and Sky1 HD.  Syfy announced the series cancellation during the mid-season hiatus. Syfy aired the remainder of season two consisting of the final 10 episodes which were all filmed before the series was cancelled. The second half of Season 2 began airing on Mondays as of March 7.<ref name=airdates/> In Canada, the second half of Season 2 began airing on Tuesdays as of March 8 at 10pm on the [[Space Channel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spacecast.com/Schedule.aspx?date=2011-03-08&mode=Daily&tz=ET|title=Space Channel 2011-03-08 Schedule|accessdate=March 4, 2011}}</ref>
{{:Stargate Universe (season 2)}}<!--Dear editor: Please go to [[Stargate Universe (season 2)]] to edit the episode summaries.-->

==Webisodes==
;{{anchor|Stargate Universe Kino}}Stargate Universe Kino

Thirty-four [[webisode]]s have also been released to tie into the series. The webisodes use "'''SG&middot;U Stargate Universe KINO'''" as their title card. They center on the Kino (described by Mallozzi as an Ancient version of the [[Earth technology in Stargate#Mobile Analytic Laboratory Probe (M.A.L.P.)|MALP]]) following around the crew of the ''Destiny''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sffchronicles.co.uk/2009/08/thirty-sgu-webisodes-on-the-way/|title=Thirty SGU webisodes on the way|first=David|last=Allen|date=August 12, 2009|accessdate=August 18, 2009|publisher=Chronicles Network}}</ref><ref name=jm_090331>{{cite web|last=Mallozzi|first=Joseph|authorlink=Joseph Mallozzi|url=http://josephmallozzi.wordpress.com/2009/03/31/march-31-2009-my-five-second-stint-as-a-camera-operator-the-kino-revealed-and-my-top-10-favorite-stargate-episode-titles/|title=March 31, 2009: My Five Second Stint as a Camera Operator, The KINO Revealed, and My Top 10 Favorite Stargate Episode Titles|work=josephmallozzi.wordpress.com|date=March 31, 2009|accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref> The webisodes are available for viewing at the [http://stargate.mgm.com/view/character/171/index.html Kino] character profile.

